{
  "stem": "24397.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And the two children of Mr.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Griggs, Charlie and Kitty, both came back to London, so there were four of us living in this house.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And we kind of knew that something had to happen, you know, we-- as far as living somewhere else.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We couldn't just continue like that.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "At first, we of course thought that maybe they'll find our parents, we'll return to our parents, and life, you know, will go back to what it was.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But by the end of '45 or '46, the news of what actually took place in Europe became fully known, and we knew that we didn't have any family left there, no aunts, uncles, no parents, no one.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "No one survived.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And it was really now up to-- up to us whether we wanted to continue to live as we were or try and pick up the pieces and try and maintain or become-- lead a Jewish life.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And probably more my sister than myself was the mover in that direction.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I guess I was quite happy with my friends and activities that went on.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But I think she was perhaps thinking about futures more seriously.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And we made-- she made contact through some friends of hers with a family from-- that brought us to Manchester.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And I think it was important to move away, because you can't have a group of friends and live one way one day one way, and then the next day say, you know, gee, I'm-- everything's changed, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] because at that time, it seemed like there was only the orthodoxy and not being Jewish.",
      "word_count": 57
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "I didn't know any in-betweens.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "So we moved to Manchester, and--",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My sister and I, yes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we took lodgings in two different homes actually.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
